---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import LearningPathwayDiagram from '../components/LearningPathwayDiagram.astro';
---
<Base
  title="VAI · Veterinary Academy International"
  description="Veterinary Academy International is the veterinary academy of Academia Europa. Structured, evidence-based postgraduate education for veterinarians and veterinary teams."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-deep text-ivory">
    <div class="container-prose py-32 md:py-44">
      <div class="eyebrow text-champagne-soft mb-8">Veterinary Academy International</div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-ivory text-5xl md:text-7xl leading-[1.02] max-w-5xl">
        Postgraduate Veterinary Education, Built for Mastery.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-10 max-w-3xl text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed text-platinum">
        VAI is the veterinary academy of Academia Europa: structured, evidence-based, expert-led education for veterinarians and veterinary teams seeking depth, progression, and lasting clinical authority.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/programmes" class="btn btn-light">Explore Programmes</a>
        <a href="/faculty" class="btn btn-light">Teach with VAI</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section eyebrow="Beyond Fragmented CPD" title="Education that progresses.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Veterinary continuing education has become an inventory of isolated hours: webinars without progression, certificates without architecture, knowledge without translation into practice. VAI was created to offer something different: a structured, expert-led, evidence-aware path from clinical competence to clinical mastery, and beyond, to leadership in the profession.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Flagship Educational Direction" title="Veterinary Longevity." tone="ivory">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-7 prose-editorial">
        <p>Veterinary Longevity is one of VAI's flagship educational directions, focused on the science-aware study of animal healthspan, early detection, preventive thinking, and responsible clinical integration. It is developed within VAI's broader postgraduate veterinary education framework, with a dedicated platform at VeterinaryLongevity.com.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="https://www.veterinarylongevity.com" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="btn">Explore Veterinary Longevity ↗</a>
          <a href="/programmes" class="btn">View VAI Programmes</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-5 border-l border-champagne pl-8 py-2">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-3">The Clinical Question</div>
        <blockquote class="font-serif italic text-2xl text-navy-deep leading-snug">
          "What does this mean on Monday morning in a real clinic?"
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="What Makes VAI Different">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-w-5xl">
      {[
        { t: 'Case-Based Teaching', d: 'Every concept tested against the realities of clinical practice.' },
        { t: 'Expert-Led Faculty', d: 'Programmes developed with experienced clinicians, educators, and subject-matter experts.' },
        { t: 'Documented Evidence', d: 'Every module grades the evidence behind its content, openly.' },
      ].map((s, i) => (
        <div>
          <div class="font-serif text-champagne text-sm tracking-[0.3em] mb-3">0{i + 1}</div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-navy-deep mb-3">{s.t}</h3>
          <p class="text-graphite leading-relaxed">{s.d}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Learning Pathways" title="Foundation. Mastery. Leadership." tone="ivory" align="center">
    <LearningPathwayDiagram />
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Leadership" title="Founder-led. Academically collaborative.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Veterinary Academy International was established under the leadership of <strong class="text-navy-deep font-medium">Dr. Soheyl Simaei</strong>, a veterinarian and educator with more than two decades of clinical, leadership, and entrepreneurial experience. VAI is being developed with experienced veterinary professionals, educators, and subject-matter experts to create structured, evidence-based postgraduate veterinary education.</p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="/about/leadership" class="inline-block text-sm tracking-[0.14em] uppercase text-navy hover:text-champagne">Read the leadership note →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Academic Discipline" title="Built with professional review readiness in mind." tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>VAI programmes are developed with defined learning objectives, structured modules, evidence-level distinctions, assessment components, faculty documentation, and reference versioning. The model is designed to support CPD/CE alignment and external professional review where applicable, with any recognition stated clearly on the relevant programme page once formally granted.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/academic-standards" class="btn">Academic Standards</a>
        <a href="/cpd-ce-alignment" class="btn">CPD/CE Alignment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="bg-navy-deep text-ivory">
    <div class="container-prose py-28 text-center">
      <div class="eyebrow text-champagne-soft mb-6">For Veterinarians, Faculty, and Institutions</div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-ivory text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        VAI is being built for veterinary professionals who want education with structure, evidence, and meaning.
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-light">Register Interest</a>
        <a href="/faculty" class="btn btn-light">Teach with VAI</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
